explanation: The code was checking the wrong set difference. It used len((fj | fi)) - len(fj) which equals |fi \ fj| (functions i has that j doesn't). The problem requires checking whether j has at least one function that i lacks, i.e. |fj \ fi|. I fixed that by replacing len((fj | fi)) - len(fj) with len((fj | fi)) - len(fi) (equivalently |fj \ fi|).
